SIMPLE: micrograph
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Micrograph
<hw>Mi"cro*graph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Micrography</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An instrument for
executing minute writing or engraving.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a graphic image, such as a photograph or drawing,
representing an object as seen with a microscope, usually much enlarged
as compared with the original object. A photograph of a microscopic
image is also called a <altname>photomicrograph</altname> or
<altname>microphotograph</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Micrographic</ent>⟦br⟧
